@startuml concern-map
' Concern map — CanvassDesktop.cs (current god MonoBehaviour) redistributed to its SRP homes.
' Text-based source per spec Section 10.4 (supersedes archived/concern-map.png, which was binary-only).
' Content source: architecture.md Section 5.1 (concerns) + 5.2 (target decomposition) + 5.3/5.4 (SOLID/GRASP rationale).

title CanvassDesktop — eight entangled concerns redistributed to their SRP homes

skinparam rectangle {
  roundCorner 12
  BackgroundColor<<god>> #FADBD8
  BorderColor<<god>> #C0392B
  BackgroundColor<<concern>> #FCF3CF
  BorderColor<<concern>> #B7950B
  BackgroundColor<<home>> #D4EFDF
  BorderColor<<home>> #1E8449
  BackgroundColor<<server>> #D6EAF8
  BorderColor<<server>> #2471A3
}

rectangle "CanvassDesktop.cs\ncurrent MonoBehaviour\n~1899 lines | WMC~63 | CBO~47 | LCOM=0.955" <<god>> as GOD

' ---- the eight concerns radiating from the god class (architecture.md Section 5.1) ----
rectangle "1. Scene-hierarchy wiring\n(transform.Find chains)" <<concern>> as C1
rectangle "2. FITS file I/O + HDU parsing" <<concern>> as C2
rectangle "3. Rendering state sync\n(Update() per-frame poll)" <<concern>> as C3
rectangle "4. Subset bounds validation" <<concern>> as C4
rectangle "5. File-dialog orchestration" <<concern>> as C5
rectangle "6. Coroutine lifecycle" <<concern>> as C6
rectangle "7. Singleton hunting\n(FindObjectOfType)" <<concern>> as C7
rectangle "8. Paint-mode state" <<concern>> as C8

GOD -- C1
GOD -- C2
GOD -- C3
GOD -- C4
GOD -- C5
GOD -- C6
GOD -- C7
GOD -- C8

' ---- the new homes (architecture.md Section 5.2) ----
rectangle "CanvassDesktopShell\ncomposition root | WMC=8 | CBO=4" <<home>> as SHELL
rectangle "FileTabViewModel\nBrowseImage / BrowseMask / LoadCube commands" <<home>> as FILEVM
rectangle "SubsetBoundsViewModel\nValidate() | IsLoadable" <<home>> as SUBVM
rectangle "RenderingTabViewModel\nobservable binding (INPC)" <<home>> as RENDERVM
rectangle "IFileDialogService\nACL adapter over StandaloneFileBrowser" <<home>> as DIALOG
rectangle "Service Gateway -> IFitsService\nserver-side FITS parse (JSON-RPC)" <<server>> as GATEWAY

' ---- each concern to its new home, arrow labelled by the principle (Section 5.3 / 5.4) ----
C1 ..> SHELL    : Creator (shell wires panels)
C7 ..> SHELL    : DIP (constructor injection)
C5 ..> FILEVM   : Controller (command in VM)
C6 ..> FILEVM   : async ICommand (Task)
C4 ..> SUBVM    : Information Expert
C3 ..> RENDERVM : SRP (push, not Update() poll)
C8 ..> RENDERVM : SRP (coord. Sub-team 4)
C2 ..> GATEWAY  : Indirection (IFitsService)

FILEVM --> SUBVM   : owns
FILEVM --> DIALOG  : delegates dialog (ACL)
FILEVM --> GATEWAY : LoadCube via gateway

legend left
  red    = current god class (1 unit, 8 reasons to change)
  yellow = the 8 concerns it conflates
  green  = new client-side SRP homes
  blue   = server-side (FITS I/O leaves the client)
endlegend

footer Source: architecture.md Section 5.1 / 5.2 / 5.4 -- supersedes archived/concern-map.png (Section 10.4 text-based requirement)

@enduml
